<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<section xml:id="sec_det_summ">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        The determinant of an <m>n \times n</m> matrix
        <m>A = [a_{ij}]</m> is found by taking the cofactor expansion of <m>A</m> along the first row.
        That is
        <me>
          \det(A) = a_{11}C_{11} + a_{12}C_{12} + a_{13}C_{13} + \cdots + a_{1n}C_{1n}
        </me>,
        where
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>A_{ij}</m> is the sub-matrix of <m>A</m> found by deleting the <m>i</m>th row and <m>j</m>th column of <m>A</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>C_{ij} = (-1)^{i+j} \det\left(A_{ij}\right)</m> is the <m>ij</m>th
              <term>cofactor</term> of <m>A</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The matrix <m>A</m> is invertible if and only if <m>\det(A) \neq 0</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>